The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for generating structured queries from natural language. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves meta-learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves techniques such as relevance functions and few-shot learning, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also deals with structured query generation, which is a subfield of database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques, which fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
